The paper discusses defending against adversarial attacks on artificial neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the limitations of a specific defense method, pixel discretization, which is a technique used in many different domains and could potentially fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
